title: For Sale:  SMITH & WESSON 39-2
postcontent:
HARD TO FIND SMITH AND WESSON 39-2 DA/SA BLUED.GREAT CONDITION FOR IT'S AGE MANUFACTURED 1980 AS PER STANDARD CATALOG OF S&W 3RD EDITION. SOME WEAR AND LOSS OF BLUING TO A NICE PETINA AS WOULD BE EXPECTED WITH A PISTOL 35 YEARS OLD. HAD TO TAKE THIS ONE TO THE RANGE AND VERIFY THE S&W FIRST GENERATION REPUTATION. PUT A BOX OF ROUNDS THROUGH IT NOT A GLITCH FED FLAWLESSLY. INCLUDES PISTOL WITH TWO(2) 8 ROUND MAGAZINES,NON ORIGINAL 39 BOX AND PAPER WORK.                                                 

THE SMITH & WESSON MODEL 39 WAS A SEMI-AUTOMATIC PISTOL DEVELOPED FOR THE US ARMY SERVICE PISTOL TRIALS OF 1954.  AFTER THE ARMY ABANDONED ITS SEARCH FOR A NEW PISTOL, THE MODEL 39 WENT ON THE CIVILIAN MARKET IN 1955 AND WAS THE FIRST OF SMITH & WESSON'S FIRST GENERATION SEMI-AUTOMATIC PISTOLS. USED BY THE ILLINOIS STATE POLICE AND THE US NAVY SEALS, IT WAS A GROUNDBREAKING PISTOL FOR USE WITH THE MILITARY AND LAW-ENFORCEMENT AGENCIES

THE SMITH & WESSON MODEL 39 WAS THE FIRST U.S. DESIGNED DOUBLE ACTION (DA) SEMI-AUTOMATIC PISTOL MARKETED IN THE UNITED STATES. THE GERMAN WALTHER P38 DA PISTOL IMPRESSED AMERICAN ORDNANCE PERSONNEL DURING WORLD WAR II. THE ARMY ORDNANCE CORPS ISSUED A PROPOSAL FOR AN AMERICAN EQUIVALENT TO THE P38. IN 1949, SMITH & WESSON BEGAN DEVELOPMENT OF THE MODEL 39 DA SEMI-AUTO IN CALIBER 9X19MM LUGER. SMITH & WESSON BEGAN SELLING THE MODEL 39 COMMERCIALLY IN 1955. THIS IS CONSIDERED A FIRST GENERATION PISTOL. SINCE THE MODEL 39 CAME OUT, S&W HAS CONTINUOUSLY DEVELOPED THE DESIGN INTO ITS THIRD GENERATION PISTOLS NOW ON THE MARKET. FIRST GENERATION MODELS USE A 2 DIGIT MODEL NUMBER, SECOND GENERATION USE 3 DIGITS, AND THIRD GENERATION MODELS USE 4 DIGITS

postcontent:
Price Reduced! Selling a custom built 338-300 WSM long range rifle. No expense was spared in the construction of this rifle. It is a Stiller Precision Predator Long Action with a 20 MOA rail. It is fitted with a 27 inch Shilen 1-9 ratchet twist Select Match #6 contour barrel. It is fitted with an American Precision Little Bastard muzzle Break. The scope is a Vortex Viper 6-24x50 PST FFP MILRAD scope with Vortex precision matched rings and bubble level. The trigger is a Timney adjustable flat blade trigger. This rifle will magazine feed with even the longest VLD solid projectiles seated to the lands.

Velocities run about 2800 fps with 250 gr bullets, 2900 fps with 225 gr bullets and close to 3300 fps with 180 gr bullets. It is a very efficient performer. Recoil is very mild and not much more than a 243 win. Total weight is about 12 lbs. You are getting very close to 338 Lapua performance burning 30% less powder in a much lighter platform. 

This rifle has about 100 rounds through it to work up load data for it. With select handloads, it routinely shoots sub 1/2 inch groups at 200 yards. title: For Sale:  Kimber of Oregon 6mm PPC Near New Condition
postcontent: In 1987, Kimber of Oregon announced a new edition to their line of rifles, the Model 84 Ultra Varmint.  Kimber only listed the 6MM PPC special world class single shot target/varmit caliber,  as a factory offering in the Ultra Varmint only, in that year. Kimber built a very few Ultra Varmint rifles chambered in the wonderfully accurate 6MM PPC. THIS IS ONE OF THOSE RARE RIFLES!!  The Ultra Varmint was (and is) a varmint style or target rifle designed to tolerate inhospitable field conditions while delivering consistent accuracy. Starting with a laminated birch stock with a straight comb and no cheekpiece, Kimber added 20 lines-per-inch checkering, a curved rubber butt pad, a widened forearm designed to provide stability, a “medium-heavy” stainless steel 24 inch varmint weight barrel, a matte blue receiver and trigger guard, a three dimensional steel grip cap in matte blue finish, and two post-style sling swivel studs. This example of the Kimber Ultra Varminter is a single shot 6MM PPC with serial number “6PPC458”, the Heavy Barrel has a bead blasted matte finish and  has a 0.6875 inch muzzle. This rifle has the Kimber disc safety and the Model 84 standard bolt, with its Mauser-style extractor and matte blue handle and shroud. A correct one piece, matte blue finish, factory provided and installed  Kimber scope ring base is on the top of the receiver waiting for your choice of scopes. Weight: ~7 pounds 12 ounces. OAL: ~42.5 inches. LOP: ~13 5/8 inches. This rifle is “as new”, and has been shot an extimated 50 rounds.  These  Varmint/target rifles do not come on the market very often, and almost never are they seen in this “almost new” condition. Ultra Varmint examples in the 6MM PPC chambering are very rare. Phone REDACTED, email: REDACTED. Contact for more detailed photos. Will ship by UPS to a Federal  licensed dealer only. So you would have to make arrangements for a dealer to accept this rifle for you.
